      "message": "I initially attempted to mock YangTextToIRSourceTransformer, but doing so caused a NullPointerException because the utility code calls .statement() on the returned AST.\n\nWhen I tried to deeply mock the returned AST (YangIRSource and IRStatement), Mockito threw a fatal MockitoException because OpenDaylight has migrated these AST representations to Java sealed classes. Mockito cannot generate proxy subclasses for sealed classes.\n\nBecause DefaultYangTextToIRSourceTransformer is a lightweight, stateless utility, instantiating the real implementation directly in the unit test is the cleanest workaround to satisfy the parser chain. (The OSGi classloading restrictions don\u0027t apply here since unit tests run on a flat classpath).",
